President Biden has declared a state of emergency in South Carolina due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Ian. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment as needed to help alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Under the Public Assistance program, 75 percent of funding will be provided for emergency protective measures. Kevin A. Wallace Sr. has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.